The paper discusses motion planning for robots, which falls under the field of robotics (cs.RO). The proposed approach involves enhancing sampling-based planning algorithms, which involves the use of artificial intelligence techniques (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the implementation of the approach on specific robots, which falls under the field of control systems (cs.SY). The experiments involve analyzing the performance of the approach, which involves the use of machine learning techniques (cs.LG) and computer vision techniques (cs.CV) for visualizing the results.
